# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js 14 App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package via npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with resolved dependencies

### 2. Code Configuration
Modified `src/app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import for Analytics component: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `{children}` element

## Implementation Details

The configuration follows the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide for Next.js App Router:
- Used the framework-specific import path: `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Placed the Analytics component in the root layout file as recommended
- Positioned the component at the end of the body tag to avoid impacting page load performance

## Verification

✅ ESLint check passed with no warnings or errors
✅ Production build completed successfully
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ All dependencies resolved correctly

## Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the project to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. After deployment, verify integration by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*` and `/<unique-path>/view`

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated dependency lock file
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics component import and usage

## Technical Notes
- The Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact page performance
- Analytics data will be collected automatically once enabled in the Vercel dashboard
- The implementation is framework-specific and optimized for Next.js App Router
- No additional configuration files are needed
